25 Jun 2010 16:30






I, personally, thought the actual effect of 513 was too reminiscent of the type of cheap scare shots you can expect at the beginning of a horror movie or during the teaser for an episode of the X-Files. You know, where we see the monster-of-the-week in reflections and so on as the person on screen goes about their business. And artifacts that cause their victims to commit suicide often smack of lazy writing, as though you couldn't think of a satisfying fate for them so you went with, eh, suicide, cuz that's always scary, right?

But I still ended up upvoting it for the addendum. I don't know why, but short verse like that, when properly done, scares the bejeezus out of me. Good job.

P.S. Not to say that the meat of the article is bad, or poorly written. I just wouldn't have upvoted for that alone.





